A woman has died in a collision between a motor vehicle and a bus on Hilton Avenue, close to the on-ramp to the N3 in Hilton. The accident occurred at around 7am on Friday. According to the Mi7 National Group, paramedics found that one person had succumbed to her injuries. She was declared dead on the scene by the team. The driver of the bus sustained moderate injuries and, after being stabilised, he was transported to a local hospital for further treatment. Several other patients sustained minor injuries but did not want to be transported to hospital. The cause of the accident is being investigated by the SAPS.